// T1273 — runtime coverage for the std `stdout` getter.
//
// A batch test cannot observe its own standard streams (the runner merges the
// test binary's stdout+stderr), so the full getter -> value->structural boxing
// -> interface dispatch -> _write_bytes -> pal_write(fd 1) path is exercised
// here as a snapshot test whose captured stdout is compared against `expected`.
// Only stdout is written (deterministic; stderr separation is pinned by the Go
// IR tests, since CombinedOutput would otherwise interleave the two fds).
main!() `test(expected: """line one
line two""") {
  stdout.write_line("line one")?^;
  stdout.write_string("line two")?^;
}
